gtest_mpi
------------------------------------------
This project provides an extension to the Google Test framework, to allow
testing of MPI enabled applications. The implementation includes a custom MPI
environment and listener, with which all test failure messages are collected on
the root process and the output includes the rank index for each failure.

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/AdhocMan/gtest_mpi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/AdhocMan/gtest_mpi/archive/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gtest_mpi-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gtest_mpi-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gtest_mpi-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gtest_mpi-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(gtest_mpi)
  /usr/include/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi.hpp
  /usr/include/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi_internal.hpp
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gtest_mpi.README
  /usr/share/doc/gtest_mpi/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/gtest_mpi/README.md

